items.title: Temasek-backed meat seller Licious seeks $2 billion IPO valuation
items.description: Delightful Gourmet Pvt., which operates Licious, is opening more brick-and-mortar stores, speeding up deliveries to take on quick commerce rivals

items.description:
The company acknowledges stakeholder concerns regarding recent disclosures to the exchanges
(NSE & BSE) and their business and operational impact

items.title: Diamond exporter Goldiam explores setting up a manufacturing facility in USA
items.description: A manufacturing facility closer to the US clients may mean Goldiam could save on shipping cost and processing, as well as avoid import tariffs on jewellery, aside of easier compliance to local regulations.

items.title: Axis Max Life aims to dial back ULIP exposure amid margin decline
items.description: Product mix shift, high ULIP sales, and new surrender norms impacted margins by 4 percent, said CFO Amrit Singh in an interaction

items.title: Production at Sriperumbudur factory remains uninterrupted, says Samsung amid escalating labour strike
items.description: A company source acknowledged that production initially dipped when the protest began but has since returned to normal

items.title: Deepak Nitrite shares extend fall amid midcap risk aversion, but DAM and Morgan Stanley have bullish targets
items.description: DAM Capital has a Buy call on Deepak Nitrite with a target of Rs 2,142 per share, while Morgan Stanley has put a target of Rs 3000 per share along with a Overweight call.

items.title: Ripe for Disruption: Opportunities and challenges in the evolving insurance sector
items.description: The insurance sector offers significant growth potential despite challenges like outdated underwriting, trust issues, and complex processes. Opportunities exist in areas such as vehicle underwriting, SMB insurance, and surety bonds, with innovation-driven startups poised to capitalise on these gaps.
